sonusAtmExtMIB.description: The MIB Module for Sonus ATM extensions.

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnTable.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnTable
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnTable.description: The Virtual Channel Link (VCL) Extension table.

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnEntry.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnEntry
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnEntry.description: An entry in the VCL Extension table. This entry adds additional objects to the atmVclTable. A row is added to this table when a row is created in the atmVclTable.

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnIfIndex.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnIfIndex
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the NIF that VCL is on.

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnVpi.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnVpi
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnVpi.description: The VPI value of the VCL.

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnVci.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnVci
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnVci.description: The VCI value of the VCL.

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnTimeout.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnTimeout
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnTimeout.description: The dryup timeout in minute. The default is one hour

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnState.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnState
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnState.description: A VCL must be enabled before System Manager will fully recognize it. The VCL must be disabled before the server module can be deleted.

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnOutOfServiceReason.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnOutOfServiceReason
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnOutOfServiceReason.description: The reason of ATM VC being out of service. The NIF could be out of service due to one of the following reasons: operator initiated command, gateway not responding to arp request, port failure/outOfService, or server failure/outOfService. The notApplicable is set when the ATM VC is inService or dryUp state

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnBwDeviation.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnBwDeviation
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnBwDeviation.description: The deviation between actual and expected VCL bandwidth in percentage of the overall VCL bandwidth. If actual bandwidth is greater than the expected bandwdith plus deviation amount, a trap will be set and the trap will be only cleared when the actual bandwidth dropped below the expected bandwidth. If the actual bandwidth is lower than the expected badniwdth minus 2 times of deviation amount, a different trap will be set and the trap will be cleared when the actual bandwdith reaches the expected bandwidth.

sonusAtmExtVclAdmnBwContingency.name: sonusAtmExtVclAdmnBwContingency
sonusAtmExtVclAdmnBwContingency.description: The percentage of the overall VCL bandwidth is reserved for contigency. If actual bandwidth is greater than the expected bandwdith and less than the overall VCL bandwidth minus contingency amount, calls will still be accepted.

sonusAtmExtVclStatTable.description: The Virtual Channel Link (VCL) Extension stat table.

sonusAtmExtVclStatEntry.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatEntry
sonusAtmExtVclStatEntry.description: An entry in the VCL Extension stat table.

sonusAtmExtVclStatIfIndex.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatIfIndex
sonusAtmExtVclStatIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the NIF that VCL is on.

sonusAtmExtVclStatVpi.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatVpi
sonusAtmExtVclStatVpi.description: The VPI value of the VCL.

sonusAtmExtVclStatVci.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatVci
sonusAtmExtVclStatVci.description: The VCI value of the VCL.

sonusAtmExtVclStatState.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatState
sonusAtmExtVclStatState.description: VCL enrties are created with a state of inService. A VCL which is outOfService has had all active calls terminated. A VCL must be outOfService in order to change its state to disabled.

sonusAtmExtVclStatCallNum.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatCallNum
sonusAtmExtVclStatCallNum.description: The number of calls on this VCL

sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedCur.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedCur
sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedCur.description: The current speed(bandwidth) allocated on this VCL

sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedMax.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedMax
sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedMax.description: The maximum speed allowed on this VCL

sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedActual.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedActual
sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedActual.description: The actual speed(bandwidth) on this VCL

sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedDeviation.name: sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedDeviation
sonusAtmExtVclStatSpeedDeviation.description: The actual speed(bandwidth) deviation on this VCL

sonusAtmExtAtmLayerTable.name: sonusAtmExtAtmLayerTable
sonusAtmExtAtmLayerTable.description: The ATM layer table. This table maps ATM layer ifIndex to a shelf, slot, and port.

sonusAtmExtAtmLayerEntry.name: sonusAtmExtAtmLayerEntry
sonusAtmExtAtmLayerEntry.description: An entry in the ATM layer table. This entry maps the ifIndex of the ATM layer to a shelf, slot and port. A row is added to this table when a SONET port is created

sonusAtmExtAtmLayerShelfIndex.name: sonusAtmExtAtmLayerShelfIndex
sonusAtmExtAtmLayerShelfIndex.description: The index for a Sonus shelf.

sonusAtmExtAtmLayerSlotIndex.name: sonusAtmExtAtmLayerSlotIndex
sonusAtmExtAtmLayerSlotIndex.description: The index for a Sonus slot.

sonusAtmExtAtmLayerPortIndex.name: sonusAtmExtAtmLayerPortIndex
sonusAtmExtAtmLayerPortIndex.description: The index for a logical ATM layer port.

sonusAtmExtAtmLayerIfIndex.name: sonusAtmExtAtmLayerIfIndex
sonusAtmExtAtmLayerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex at the ATM layer for this shelf, slot, and port.

sonusAtmExtAtmLayerRowStatus.name: sonusAtmExtAtmLayerRowStatus
sonusAtmExtAtmLayerRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, delete, or modify a row in this table.

sonusAtmExtAal5LayerTable.name: sonusAtmExtAal5LayerTable
sonusAtmExtAal5LayerTable.description: The AAL5 layer table. This table maps AAL5 layer ifIndex to a shelf, slot, and port.

sonusAtmExtAal5LayerEntry.name: sonusAtmExtAal5LayerEntry
sonusAtmExtAal5LayerEntry.description: An entry in the AAL5 layer table. This entry maps the ifIndex of the AAL5 layer to a shelf, slot and port. A row is added to this table when a SONET port is created

sonusAtmExtAal5LayerShelfIndex.name: sonusAtmExtAal5LayerShelfIndex
sonusAtmExtAal5LayerShelfIndex.description: The index for a Sonus shelf.

sonusAtmExtAal5LayerSlotIndex.name: sonusAtmExtAal5LayerSlotIndex
sonusAtmExtAal5LayerSlotIndex.description: The index for a Sonus slot.

sonusAtmExtAal5LayerPortIndex.name: sonusAtmExtAal5LayerPortIndex
sonusAtmExtAal5LayerPortIndex.description: The index for a logical AAL5 layer port.

sonusAtmExtAal5LayerIfIndex.name: sonusAtmExtAal5LayerIfIndex
sonusAtmExtAal5LayerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex at the AAL5 layer for this shelf, slot, and port.

sonusAtmExtAal5LayerRowStatus.name: sonusAtmExtAal5LayerRowStatus
sonusAtmExtAal5LayerRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, delete, or modify a row in this table.

sonusAtmExtOamF5Table.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5Table
sonusAtmExtOamF5Table.description: A list of ATM OAM F5 entries.

sonusAtmExtOamF5Entry.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5Entry
sonusAtmExtOamF5Entry.description: An entry of sonusAtmExtOamF5Table which is used to provide OAM feature for Virtual circuit in this ATM interface. Three major OAM functions are supported in this MIB entry. The first function is the Loopback capability for this virtual circuit which includes both of End2end Loopback and UNILoopback. The second function is the OAM continuity capability for this virtual circuit which uses Loopback cells to transmit periodically. Transmit and recieve loopback cell statisitics can be used to determine if there is continuity. The third function is basic fault management feature using AIS/RDI cells to inform the upstream/downstream failure condition, the counters are used to keep failure statistics.

sonusAtmExtOamF5Vpi.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5Vpi
sonusAtmExtOamF5Vpi.description: The virtual path identifier of this entry

sonusAtmExtOamF5Vci.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5Vci
sonusAtmExtOamF5Vci.description: The virtual circuit identifier of this entry

sonusAtmExtOamF5Enable.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5Enable
sonusAtmExtOamF5Enable.description: This objects is used to enable or disable the F5 OAM loopback cells. Whenever this object is set to enable, at least one F5 OAM loopback cell will be sent. If the loopback timer is non-zero, then F5 OAM loopback cells will be sent continuosly at the interval defined by the loopback timer to perform a continuity test.

sonusAtmExtOamF5LoopbackType.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5LoopbackType
sonusAtmExtOamF5LoopbackType.description: This object is used to define the F5 OAM loopback type for this virtual circuit. Loopback cells may be sent to the local UNI or end to end.

sonusAtmExtOamF5LoopbackTimer.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5LoopbackTimer
sonusAtmExtOamF5LoopbackTimer.description: This object is used to define the time between OAM F5 loopback cells. If this object is set to zero, then a single F5 OAM cell will be sent every time the sonusAtmOamF5Enable object is set to enable. If this obkect is non-zero, then loopback cells will be sent continuously at the interval defined by this object to perform a continuity test.

sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndLoopbackFa.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndLoopbackFailure
sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndLoopbackFa.description: This is a counter object to collect the end2endLoopback failure statistics for this virtual circuit. It counts end to end F5 OAM loopback cells received with an error.

sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveUNILoopbackFailur.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveUNILoopbackFailure
sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveUNILoopbackFailur.description: This is a counter object to collect the UNILoopback failure statistics for this virtual circuit. It counts UNI F5 OAM loopback cells received with an error.

sonusAtmExtOamF5TransmitEnd2EndLoopback.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5TransmitEnd2EndLoopback
sonusAtmExtOamF5TransmitEnd2EndLoopback.description: This is a counter object to collect the all transmitted end2endLoopback statistics for this virtual circuit. It counts end to end F5 OAM loopback cells sent.

sonusAtmExtOamF5TransmitUNILoopback.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5TransmitUNILoopback
sonusAtmExtOamF5TransmitUNILoopback.description: This is a counter object to collect the all transmitted UNILoopback statistics for this virtual circuit. It counts UNI F5 OAM loopback cells sent.

sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndLoopback.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndLoopback
sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndLoopback.description: This is a counter object to collect the all received end2endLoopback statistics for this virtual circuit. It counts good end to end F5 OAM loopback cells received.

sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveUNILoopback.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveUNILoopback
sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveUNILoopback.description: This is a counter object to collect the all received UNILoopback statistics for this virtual circuit. It counts good UNI F5 OAM loopback cells received.

sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndAIS.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndAIS
sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndAIS.description: This is a counter object to collect the end2endAIS cells received in this virtual circuit.

sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndRDI.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndRDI
sonusAtmExtOamF5ReceiveEnd2EndRDI.description: This is a counter object to collect the end2endRDI cells received in this virtual circuit.

sonusAtmExtOamF5TransmitEnd2EndRDI.name: sonusAtmExtOamF5TransmitEnd2EndRDI
sonusAtmExtOamF5TransmitEnd2EndRDI.description: This is a counter object to collect the end2endRDI cells transmit in this virtual circuit.

sonusAtmExtVclInServiceNotification.name: sonusAtmExtVclInServiceNotification
sonusAtmExtVclInServiceNotification.description: This trap indicates that an ATM VC is available to support call processing.

sonusAtmExtVclOutOfServiceNotification.name: sonusAtmExtVclOutOfServiceNotification
sonusAtmExtVclOutOfServiceNotification.description: This trap indicates that an ATM VC is no longer available to support call processing.

sonusAtmExtVclEnabledNotification.name: sonusAtmExtVclEnabledNotification
sonusAtmExtVclEnabledNotification.description: This trap indicates that an ATM VC's configuration is enabled.

sonusAtmExtVclDisabledNotification.name: sonusAtmExtVclDisabledNotification
sonusAtmExtVclDisabledNotification.description: This trap indicates that an ATM VC's configuration is disabled.

sonusAtmExtVclDeletedNotification.name: sonusAtmExtVclDeletedNotification
sonusAtmExtVclDeletedNotification.description: This trap indicates that an ATM VC's configuration is deleted.

sonusAtmExtVclHighWatermarkNotification.name: sonusAtmExtVclHighWatermarkNotification
sonusAtmExtVclHighWatermarkNotification.description: This trap indicates that an ATM VC's high watermark has been reached the first time since the ATM VC's low watermark has beend reached.

sonusAtmExtVclLowWatermarkNotification.name: sonusAtmExtVclLowWatermarkNotification
sonusAtmExtVclLowWatermarkNotification.description: This trap indicates that an ATM VC's low watermark has been reached the first time since the ATM VC's high watermark has been reached.

sonusAtmExtVclBwHighDeviationNotificatio.name: sonusAtmExtVclBwHighDeviationNotification
sonusAtmExtVclBwHighDeviationNotificatio.description: This trap indicates that a VCL's actual bandwidth is greater than the expected bandwidth plus deviation amount. This trap will be re-armed when the actual bandwdith dropped below the expected level.

sonusAtmExtVclBwLowDeviationNotification.name: sonusAtmExtVclBwLowDeviationNotification
sonusAtmExtVclBwLowDeviationNotification.description: This trap indicates that a VCL's actual bandwidth is lower than the expected bandwidth minus 2 times the deviation amount.This trap will be re-armed when the actual bandwdith reached the expected level.
